        descLong: "Apache Airflow is the standard orchestration platform for data pipelines. DAGs (Directed Acyclic Graphs) define task dependencies and schedules. The TaskFlow API (@dag, @task decorators) is the modern Pythonic way to write DAGs. Operators execute specific actions: PythonOperator (run Python), BashOperator (shell commands), and provider-specific operators (S3, BigQuery, Snowflake). Sensors wait for external conditions (file exists, API available). XCom passes data between tasks. Connections store credentials securely.",
