        descLong: "PySpark lets you write SQL queries against DataFrames. createOrReplaceTempView() registers a DataFrame as a temporary view (valid for the session). spark.sql() executes SQL and returns a new DataFrame. Use SQL when it's more readable than DataFrame API, or for complex joins/window functions. createGlobalTempView() persists across sessions (rare). SQL queries are optimized by Catalyst optimizer — same performance as DataFrame API.",
